            <title>[SPARK-20615] SparseVector.argmax throws IndexOutOfBoundsException when the sparse vector has a size greater than zero but no elements defined.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-20615</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.spark.ml.linalg.SparseVector.argmax throws an IndexOutOfRangeException when the vector size is greater than zero and no values are defined.  The toString() representation of such a vector is &quot; (100000,[],[])&quot;.  This is because the argmax function tries to get the value at indexes(0) without checking the size of the array.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Code inspection reveals that the mllib version of SparseVector should have the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
